Nigeria Approves Proposed Buy of Intercontinental, Vanguard Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-07-25T08:18:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-25/nigeria-approves-proposed-buy-of-intercontinental-vanguard-says.html
Nigeria’s Security and Exchange
Commission approved   Access Bank Plc (ACCESS) ’s proposed acquisition of
 Intercontinental Bank Plc (INTERCON) , a lender bailed out by the nation’s
central bank in 2009,  Vanguard  newspaper reported, citing Lanre
Oloyi, a spokesman for the Abuja-based commission.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  